Resources

Books

     * Don Tapscott, Anthony D. Williams:
       [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikinomics]Wikinomics

Articles

     * Paul Graham: [http://www.paulgraham.com/opensource.html]What
       business can learn from open source
     * Massimo Menichinelli:
       [http://www.openp2pdesign.org/2011/open-design/business-models-for-
       open-hardware/]Business models for open hardware
     * Roger Clarke: [http://www.rogerclarke.com/EC/Bled04.html]Open
       source software and open content as models for eBusiness
     * Chris Anderson:
       [http://www.longtail.com/the_long_tail/2009/01/a-business-mode.html
       ]A business model for open source hardware
     * The Economist: [http://www.economist.com/node/5624944]Open-source
       business: Open, but not as usual
     * Chad Whitacre:
       [https://medium.com/gratipay-blog/the-second-open-company-4cbab7ca1
       a47]The second open company
     * Timothy Cook:
       [https://medium.com/open-companies/why-open-companies-fdb74d1b4f0f]
       Why open companies? A new culture of business
     * Shereef Bishay:
       [http://www.opencompany.org/resources/whitepaper.pdf]The open
       enterprise manifesto

